The oral cavity is bounded by (Figure 52):
● Anteriorly by the lips;
● Posteriorly by the palatoglossal arches (anterior pillars of the fauces);
● Laterally by the teeth and cheeks;
● Inferiorly by the floor of mouth and mylohyoid;
● Superiorly by the hard palate.

Signs
● Pyrexia;
● Swollen tonsils +/- exudate;
● Thick or ‘hot potato’ voice with enlarged tonsils;
● Presence of trismus indicates a peritonsillar abscess (quinsy);
● Bilateral cervical lymphadenopathy.

